1.
    r1: love can always find a way (len = 6)
    r2: love makes anything possible (len = 4)
    c1: the love can always do (len = 5)
     n=1 :  3/5
       numerator: 0 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 0
     denominator: 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1
     n=2: 2/4 
       numerator: 0 + 1 + 1 + 0
     denominator: 1 + 1 + 1 + 1   
     BP : exp(1 - (4/5))
     
    BLEU (c1) := exp(1-(4/5)) * (0.5 * sum([3/5,2/4])) = 0.67177
    
    r1: love can always find a way (len = 6)
    r2: love makes anything possible (len = 4)
    c2: love can make anything possible (len = 5)
     n=1 :   4/5
       numerator: 1 + 1 + 0 + 1 + 1
     denominator: 1 + 1 + 1 + 1 + 1
     n=2: 2/4 
       numerator: 1 + 0 + 0 + 1
     denominator: 1 + 1 + 1 + 1   
      BP : exp(1 - (4/5))
     
     BLEU (c1) := exp(1-(4/5)) * (0.5 * sum([4/5,2/4])) = 0.79391
     
     c2 wins according to BLEU, altough c1 has closest meaning.
     
